2 §1300.41. Citizens Advisory Referendum; Petition
3 A.(1) A parish governing authority may hold a parish wide referendum for
4 advisory purposes if at least ten percent of registered voters within the parish sign
5 a petition expressing their desire to have a certain matter on the ballot.
6 (2) Whenever a citizens advisory referendum is sought by the registered
7 voters within a parish, a petition shall be directed to the parish governing authority.
8 The petition shall be limited to the request that an election be called and held in the
9 parish for the purpose of putting a question on the ballot. No petition for a citizens
10 advisory referendum shall seek to put more than one question on the ballot.
11 (3) The secretary of state shall provide a form approved by the attorney
12 general to be used for the petition to call a citizens advisory referendum. Such form
13 shall include pre-printed line numbers and shall be in conformity with all other
14 provisions of this Chapter and R.S. 18:3. All citizens advisory referendum petitions
15 shall be on an approved form or on a form which contains the same information
16 required by the approved form, and any petition not on such a form shall be invalid.
